details.description: Relaxed spot serving high-end coffee drinks, plus tea & light fare in an airy space with a patio.

raw_data.name: Not Just Coffee
raw_data.full_address: 421 Providence Rd, Charlotte, NC 28207, United States
raw_data.description: Relaxed spot serving high-end coffee drinks, plus tea & light fare in an airy space with a patio.
raw_data.typical_time_spent: People typically spend up to 2.5 hours here

reviews_data.review_text:
It’s in the name, not just coffee but also not… I’m traveling and needed a place to get some work done before getting on the road. There’s a small very narrow bar along the windows with wobbly chairs and the only other option was to sit on the porch next to the loud road. This place is probably better for just taking your drink to go, not necessarily inviting to stay/spend more.

The barista “accidentally” let me sit in the “gallery” but the receptionist who was MIA when I first came in then notified me that I couldn’t sit there after popping out of the backroom and suddenly she was back at her little desk. Men’s clothing looked cute but there seemed to be a meeting going on in the shop area. Kind of just a stale vibe.  The barista was very nice and pleasant.

I’m not a coffee drinker so I can’t speak on how good theirs is, however I did have their teas and was very pleased. This location is very serene. I enjoyed looking at their collections of books while my tea was brewing. My interaction with the lady at the register was also pleasant. Will return.

My husband doesn’t get excited about anything. But every drink of his macchiato so far he’s said “this is LIFE CHANGING” or “I’m gonna chase this high till I die now.” 😂
But seriously, skip the Starbucks. This coffee is AMAZING.
The shop is so cute too! Art, books, clothing, everything. It’s more than coffee, but they totally get the coffee right!!

As a chef, I always look for a perfectly balanced cappuccino, just like I like my wine-- not too acidic, not bitter, but rounded and nutty, full of depth-- and when it can be done with almond milk (since I'm sadly dairy intolorant), a coffee shop knows what they're doing. Not Just Coffee does it perfectly 🤌🤌

The ambiance inside is delightful, but the outdoor "hidden nook" surrounded by vines is my favorite.
Very cozy.

I had an amazing experience at this coffee shop on my first visit, and I’m definitely coming back! The barista was incredibly sweet, making the atmosphere even more warm and welcoming. The space itself is calm and friendly, perfect for relaxing or getting some work done. I especially loved the opportunity to appreciate the art inside and enjoy nature while sitting on the patio—such a great spot, especially now that the weather is warming up. I ordered a caramel latte, and it was absolutely delicious! I went to study, and it was the perfect setting.

Good coffee, well served, the place is too noisy it’s not easy for a conversation, but good decoration inside.
Nice place for a coffee break

A friend and I stopped by to check out the art. We were able to grab some delicious pastries and I had a latte. Both were so delicious. The atmosphere was fun. Beautiful art to buy and gift shop things. The staff were so nice.

We decided to visit some place in Charlotte.   Before we visited SOCO Gallery, we thought to stop and get coffee at Not Just Coffee.   To our surprise,  they are together in one building space.  My daughter ordered an iced matcha latte with oat milk and I ordered a hot mocha latte with oat milk.   They were delicious!  Ethan took great care of us!  He was so sweet,  friendly and helpful!   We really enjoyed talking with him!  If and when we visit Charlotte again,  we will definitely stop here again!
Delicious. Great iced latte. I appreciate the milk alternatives and gluten free bread. Everything was great. Can’t wait to go back.

Visited the place yesterday. My cappuccino was enjoyable (milk was steamed properly and the temperature was right (hate when it's too hot as most do). The batch brew was balanced and very tasty. The barista was very friendly.
I would say this is a specialty coffee spot and unfortunately there are only few coffee shops in Charlotte area where you can find truly specialty coffee.
Thank you!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the wonderful review! I will pass it on to the team - James Yoder (owner)

reviews_data.review_text: Coffee sucks! Terrible attitudes!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey Adam, you left us a terrible 1* review six days ago at another location. Presumably your spouse or family member also left a bad review. I refunded and apologized but at this point it feels like you’re trolling. You stated in your previous review that you hated it and wouldn’t be back yet here you are 6 days later leaving another bad review. I know the small team at our Tabor location and while not perfect, they are incredibly kind and sympathetic people. Maybe they were having an off day or there was a misunderstanding. Either way after refunding you and apologizing, I’m not sure what you’re looking for, feel free to not patronize my business if you feel we are that awful. 
Here’s my email again if you need to discuss further. James@notjust.coffee

James Yoder

reviews_data.review_text: If I could give 0 stars I would.  Got our order wrong then asked if I wanted her to remake it - when I said yes please we ordered (x) she rolled her eyes and grabbed the cup. Horrible service definitely avoid
Overall awesome place!
I’ll dream about the homemade caramel syrup for the rest of my life.
One person working so during rushes it takes a bit which is understandable. Amazing iced oat milk caramel latte. Seriously so amazing
I like the atmosphere and the coffee/ gallery space
I ordered mocha, Not a good one
What a great coffee spot.. loved the atmosphere and LOVED the coffee.  The rhubarb cake was delicious!
Good coffee. The gallery and store are nice to peruse while you sip. Wanted to use this as a work location but it’s quaint so my team wouldn’t be able to spread out like we usually do.

I popped in to Not Just Coffee for a quick cortado (which was delicious hence why I started drinking it before I remembered to take a photo), and discovered that they not only have great coffee, but a beautiful art gallery as well as a men's clothing store that carried some handsome clothing articles on a pretty big discount (70% off). I felt very welcome, and the ambiance was lovely. I will be back!
Don't take cash? Tiny parking lot not for full sized trucks.

This place is very cute and unique; a welcome site for Charlotte.

Unfortunately, my family and I had a negative experience with the barista on shift. When ordering a drink, we were told that our definition of that specific drink was wrong and “Americanized.” Last time I checked, we live in America. Classic pretentious barista behavior that creates a bad stereotype of these otherwise cool cafes.

This location could be great but is consistently a let down. It is never open at 7:30 as the hours state it should be. Not sure what the point of a coffee shop is that isn’t open in the morning. Better off going elsewhere.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Brandon! Really sorry to hear that, can you let me know the dates that happened if you remember? Feel free to email me at james@notjust.coffee. Thanks!

reviews_data.review_text: Super cute little shop, small but straight forward menu. It shares space with 2 other business. Very nice tranquil vibe. Loved it. Barista was super nice and helped me out with recommendations.
Favorite local coffee grab, soon-to-be Night Swim Coffee, located in hip art gallery space (which also has a great art + design coffee table book selection). Cool outdoor area as well 👍
Best caramel latte I've ever had. They make their own syrups!!
A cute little stand inside the art gallery and business. Despite the name, this particular location does have just coffee ☕
The best coffee I’ve ever have tried!! Their Carmel lattes are the best!!!
interior had a musty smell, no employees in sight, waited 5 minutes and left without ordering. only one selection of pastry, nothing else. don't go to this location, parking is sketchy anyway.
Always consistently a great couple of coffee - one of Charlotte's best!
Great matcha lattes
They have the strongest espresso I have ever had.
This is a small booth next to an art gallery. Be prepared for tight parking and a possible wait since there is only one barista. That being said the coffee and atmosphere was wonderful.

This is a unique coffee shop. Not Just Coffee is hands down the best and most consistent coffee shop in Charlotte. Their baristas are friendly and know their stuff. This particular location is quieter than most. I asked El, the barista to make me a swan and she nailed it 😊
Was expecting it to be a larger version of the one uptown, but it didn't serve any of the yummy food.  Disappointed
This is my go-to spot for coffee when I want to sit outside and enjoy the sun. Their iced caramel latte is my favorite and I’ll miss it when I move this summer. 😟
Good coffee and friendly service
Cutest little spot. Great coffee! Emma was super friendly and introduced me to Oat milk! I will be returning!
This is one of the  best brands in Charlotte. And this location is a nice change of pace from their other spots. Will be coming back soon
If you enjoy quality coffee, then NJC needs to be on your list
Best coffee in the city
Always a great experience. No matter the drink you choose, it will be the best you ever tasted.
Excellent food
